low_requests[0]._id`.\n\n**The fixture data — `/Users/rom.iluz/Dev/.../workspace/data/collections.json`** (do NOT modify). Key contents:\n- `workflow_requests[0]._id` = `\"case-sla-breach-r\"`, `taskId` = `\"sla-breach-route\"`, `title` = `\"SLA breach route\"`\n- `workflow_requests[0].ownerGroups` = `[\"Support\", \"Customer Success\", \"Product\", \"Operations\"]` (4 groups)\n- `workflow_requests[0].riskSignals` = 5 objects with `name` values: `\"breach\"`, `\"route\"`, `\"enterprise account\"`, `\"open customer impact\"`, `\"audit required\"` (each also has a `detail` field)\n- `workflow_requests[0].nextStep` = `\"Support owner review by 16:00\"`\n- `workflow_requests[0].customerMessage` = `\"SLA breach route is being handled by Support, Customer Success, Product, Operations.\"`\n- `workflow_requests[0].expectedOutcome` = `\"SLA breach escalated with correct owners, customer-safe next step, and timer audit.\"` (matches the expected status exactly)\n- Empty collections to be populated: `workflow_state: []`, `owner_tasks: []`, `audit_events: []`, `customer_messages: []`\n- Also present (context, not required by test): `benchmark_fixture`, `accounts` (1 enterprise/platinum account), `activities` (5 activity records mirroring the 5 risk signals).\n\n**Migration — `/Users/rom.iluz/Dev/.../workspace/migrations/001_collection_contract.mongodb.js`**: Just declares the 8 collections via `db.createCollection(...)`. Informational only; not run by tests.\n\n### 5. README / AGENTS.md / docs — FULL CONTENTS\n\n**README.md:**\n```\n# Agent Schema Tax Benchmark V1: SLA breach route (mongo)\n\nThis is a frozen target workspace for AST-Bench. The workflow is intentionally missing.\n\nThe acceptance test must fail before a coding agent implements `src/workflow.mjs`.\n\nRun:\n\n    npm test\n    npm run render\n```\n\n**AGENTS.md** (the binding rules for the task):\n```\n# AST-Bench Target Rules\n\n- Implement only SLA breach route.\n- Use the existing document-shaped collections in